QueryText: Farmer needs information regarding WATER MANAGEMENT in wheat?
KccAns:
Recommended for the crop requires 4-6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall.Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
1.Immediately after sowing
2.Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
3.Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
4.Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
5.Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
6.Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: Farmer wants to know information about WATER MANAGEMENT in wheat?
KccAns:
Recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

KccAns:
It must first choose which room to be dark, and be neat.
 before 2 days   fumigate room  with formeldyhehyde.
Take wheat, soybean straw or rice straw {not older than 1 year], 
Soak it overnight in 50 liters of water + 3 grams bavistin +75 formalin   solution  then decant it before 2 hours of spanning.
Seprate the seed by crushing them. And fill uppermost and lowermost layer completely with span but in middile laye surface only pot in pripheral region followed by 2-2 inch straw layer . Make 2-3 holes in lower side and 10-15 holes in whole bag, and put it in a slanting surface to get out of remaining water .
After 15-20 days when whitish covering occurs hen hang it on bamboos and irrigate them every evening . Do not get them dried .
Check it out daily when mushroom came ,start picking of mushroom . Do not take too much time ot pick

QueryText: farmer want to know information about WATER MANAGEMENT in wheat?
KccAns:
recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: Farmer needs information regarding WATER MANAGEMENT in wheat?
KccAns:
Recommended for the crop requires 4-6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall.Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
1.	Immediately after sowing
2.	Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
3.	Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
4.	Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
5.	Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
6.	Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: farmer want to know about Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana?
KccAns: The premium under the Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana is way less than the previous government or private crop insurance schemes. The premium amount for Kharif crops is 2 percent and 1.5 percent or the sum insured for Rabi crops. Karif and Rabi covers most food crops and oil crops cultivated in India. The premium for commercial or horticultural crops (including cotton) is pegged at 5 percent for one year.

QueryText: Farmer needs information regarding WATER MANAGEMENT IN WHEAT CROP?
KccAns:
Farmer needs information regarding WATER MANAGEMENT 
Recommended for the crop requires 4-6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall.Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
1.	Immediately after sowing
2.	Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
3.	Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
4.	Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
5.	Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
6.	Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: Farmer needs information regarding about irrigation in cumin ?
KccAns:
Immediately after the sowing of cumin should be given a light irrigation.
Keep in mind that during irrigation, the flow of water does not accelerate or else the seed flow will get busy due to rapid drift. By the end of one week of the sowing of irrigation, when the seed starts flowing.
If sprouting is not done after the second irrigation or the crust on the ground, then a light irrigation will be beneficial.
After this, the irrigation of 5 irrigations will be sufficient from 15 to 25 days according to the nature of the land and the weather.

QueryText: Farmer Wants know information about  waste decomposer?
KccAns: Dear farmer to use, add 200 liter water to 2 kg of jaggery and mix it well. Keep it for two days in summer and 4 days in winter. After this it is ready to use. Then mix one bucket solution with 200 liters of water in this hundred liters solution. Keep this solution in this way and keep adding this solution to the water while irrigating the fields. Drip irrigation can also be used with this solution. This will spread to the entire farm. Apart from this, once a month, the waste decomposer can be sprayed to remove the disease of crops.

QueryText: farmer wants to know information about waste material compost ?
KccAns:
How to prepare waste decomposer solution from the started culture?
Take 2 kg jaggery and mixed it in a plastic drum containing 200 liters water.
Now take 1 bottle of waste decomposer and pour all its contents in a plastic drum containing jaggery solution. Avoid direct contact of contents with hands.
Mix it properly with a wooden stick for uniform distribution of waste decomposer in a drum.
Cover the drum with a paper or cardboard and stir it every day once or twice.
After 5 days the solution of drum turns creamy.
Farmers could prepare the waste decomposer solution again and again from the above formed solution. For this, 20 liter of waste decomposer solution is added to a drum with 2 kg of jaggery and 20 liter water is added. Farmers can prepare continuously this solution from this waste decomposer for lifetime.

QueryText: Farmer wants to know information about WATER MANAGEMENT in wheat?
KccAns:
Recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: Farmer wants to know information about WATER MANAGEMENT in wheat?
KccAns:
Recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: farmer want about jai kisan ren mafi yojna ?
KccAns: With the introduction of the scheme, now farmers can apply for loan waiver by filling the form. From February 22, the amount will start reaching farmers' accounts. The benefit of the scheme will be to the farmers who have taken loan from the bank under the fertilizer-seed or KYC. Applications received from live portal farmers by online MP will be updated online. Farmers will be kept in three categories, green list, white list and pink list. The green list will be the names of the farmers who are linked to their base accounts. The white list will be the names of those farmers, whose accounts do not have a base link and they will be farmers in the pink list, whose names are incorrectly written in both these lists or the names are not there. The farmer who comes in the category will have to fill the form of that color, the farm farmer will get free. Gram Panchayat Bhavan and Ward Office will be listed on the list of borrower farmers

QueryText: Farmer wants to know information about irrigation of wheat crop?
KccAns:
Recommended for the crop requires 4-6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall.Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
1.Immediately after sowing
2.Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
3.Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
4.Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
5.Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
6.Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: farmer want to know information about WATER MANAGEMENT in wheat?
KccAns:
recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

QueryText: farmer needs information regarding water management in wheat?
KccAns:
Recommended for the crop requires 4-6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall.wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
1.immediately after sowing
2.crown root initiation: 15-20 das
3.active tillering stage: 35-40 das
4.flowering stage: 50-55 das
5.grain filling stage: 70-75 das
6.crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.
